{{Infobox historical event |Event_Name = Death and state funeral of Heydar Aliyev |Image_Name = Церемония прощания с Гейдаром Алиевым. Возложение венка.jpg |Image_Caption = The coffin with the body of Heydar Aliyev [[Heydar Aliyev Palace|Palace of the Republic]] |AKA = |Participants = |Location = [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]] |Date = 15 December 2003 | burial = [[Alley of Honor]] }} [[Heydar Aliyev]], the former [[President of Azerbaijan]], died on 12 December 2003 in the [[Cleveland Clinic]] (United States) at 10 am local time from [[heart failure]]<ref>[http://www.kp.ru/daily/23175.5/25329/ Умер Гейдар Алиев]</ref> at the age of 80. December 13, Azerbaijani President [[Ilham Aliyev]] signed a decree on the establishment of the State Commission for the funeral of Heydar Aliyev.<ref>[http://files.preslib.az/site/decrees1.pdf Azərbaycan Respublikası Prezidentinin Fərmanları və Sərəncamları. Biblioqrafik göstərici № 1]</ref> December 14 the coffin of the deceased was taken to Baku.<ref>{{cite news | title=Траур |publisher=Газета «Коммерсантъ»|author= Сергей Строкань | url=http://www.kommersant.ru/doc.aspx?fromsearch=917f3b65-6ff2-468d-a1eb-103b26403c44&docsid=435636}}</ref>
[[File:Путин c Президентом Азербайджана Ильхамом Алиевым во время церемонии прощания с Гейдаром Алиевым.jpg|thumb|Ilham Aliyev with Vladimir Putin during the funeral.]] Farewell ceremony was held December 15, 2003 at the Palace of the Republic (nowadays [[Heydar Aliyev Palace]]) and was broadcast live on the main Azerbaijani TV channels. The ceremony was attended by current and former heads of states ([[Vladimir Putin]], [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]], [[Eduard Shevardnadze]], [[Leonid Kuchma]], [[Ahmet Necdet Sezer]], [[Süleyman Demirel]] etc.). Also, a number of Heads of State expressed their condolences. Heydar Aliyev was buried in the [[Alley of Honor]] next to his wife [[Zarifa Aliyeva]]. During the funerals artillery salute was given.<ref name="ng">[http://www.ng.ru/forum/forum3/topic46770/ Владимир Путин попрощался с Гейдаром Алиевым]</ref>
