{{Infobox book | name = The Impossible | author = Joyce Smith | image = The Impossible Book (Joyce Smith) cover photo.jpg | caption = | country = United States | language = English | genre = Faith Drama, Non-fiction | publisher = | release_date = November 7, 2017 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]] & [[Paperback]]) | pages = | isbn = 1478976950 | website = http://www.theimpossiblebook.com/ }}
'''''The Impossible: The Miraculous Story of a Mother's Faith and Her Child's Resurrection''''' is a [[Christian literature|Christian novel]] written by American author Joyce Smith, alongside contributor Ginger Kolbaba. The book, released on November 7, 2017, tells the story of Joyce's 14-year-old son John, who fell through icy [[Lake St. Louis, Missouri|Lake Ste. Louise]] in Missouri.<ref>{{cite news|title=Boy who fell through ice at Lake Sainte Louise is awake, recognizing people, officials say|url=http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/stcharles/boy-who-fell-through-ice-at-lake-sainte-louise-is/article_8c0ffb76-be53-5a19-b766-eb88fb9bd4e1.html|accessdate=March 6, 2018|work=St. Louis Post-Dispatch|date=January 21, 2015}}</ref>
== Plot summary == When Joyce Smith's fourteen-year-old son John fell through an icy [[Lake St. Louis, Missouri|Missouri lake]] one winter morning, she and her family had seemingly lost everything. At the hospital, John lay lifeless for more than sixty minutes. But Joyce was not ready to give up on her son. She mustered all her faith and strength into one force and cried out to God in a loud voice to save him. Miraculously, her son's heart immediately started beating again.
In the coming days, John would continue to defy every expert, every case history, and every scientific prediction. Sixteen days after falling through the ice and being clinically dead for an hour, he walked out of the hospital under his own power, completely healed.
== Film adaptation == [[20th Century Fox]] has announced plans to produce a movie adaptation of ''The Impossible'', titled '''''The Breakthrough''''', working with director [[Roxann Dawson]], executive producer [[Samuel Rodriguez]] and producer [[DeVon Franklin]], who has worked on other faith drama titles such as [[Miracles from Heaven (film)|''Miracles from Heaven'']] and [[Heaven Is for Real (film)|''Heaven Is for Real'']].<ref>{{cite news|title=Fox & DeVon Franklin Set Miracle Tale 'The Impossible'|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/john-smith-the-impossible-devon-franklin-miracle-tale-grant-nieporte-1201889423/|accessdate=March 6, 2018|work=deadline.com|date=January 18, 2017}}</ref> The film is expected to be released April 12, 2019.
In March of 2018, it was announced that actor [[Topher Grace]] will star as Pastor Jason Noble, and first responder Tommy Shine will be portrayed by [[Mike Colter]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ImpossibleBook|url=https://www.facebook.com/theimpossiblebook/posts/604797109855208|accessdate=March 16, 2018|work=Facebook|date=March 14, 2018}}</ref> Actress [[Chrissy Metz]] of [[NBC]]'s [[This Is Us (TV series)|''This Is Us'']] is set to star as Joyce Smith.<ref>{{cite news|title='This Is Us' Star Chrissy Metz Joins Faith Drama 'The Impossible'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/is-us-star-chrissy-metz-joins-impossible-1080862|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|accessdate=March 6, 2018|work=Hollywood Reporter|date=February 1, 2018}}</ref>
